\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003eゲストスピーカーの人数\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e1\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e履修選抜・課題タイプ=テキスト登録可\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003efalse\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e履修選抜・選抜課題タイプ=ファイル登録可\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003efalse\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003eGIGAサティフィケート対象\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003etrue\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"background-color: #F5F5F5; border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e最終更新日\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd style=\"border-color: #C7CDD1;\"\u003e2020/08/10 22:38:01\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n  \u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"background-color: #394B58; color: white; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e科目概要\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis introductory course surveys approaches to second language (L2) learning and factors that influence its rate and route such as cross-linguistic influence, age and individual differences. Students will discover how humans learn language(s) after they acquire their first language (L1). Students are expected to actively participate in discussions as well as taking turns in leading the discussion on various topics covered in class. \u003cbr\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 style=\"background-color: #394B58; color: white; padding-left: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e授業シラバス\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; margin-top: 0; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e主題と目標／授業の手法など\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn order to gain a basic understanding of what it means to learn second language (L2) and how it can be taught, the course will cover the following topics.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLanguage learning theories, Bilingualism, Factors affecting L2 learning,  Classroom observations, L2 teaching methodologies\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe textbook to be used for this course will be Lightbown, P.M and N. Spada (2013) How languages are learned. Oxford: Oxford University Press, 4th edition, and various reading materials.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eStudents will read the book, answer task sheets, receive lectures, choose a topic of L2 study and conduct a group project (pilot study).\u003cbr\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e教材・参考文献\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLightbown, P.M. and N. Spada (2013) How languages are learned. Oxford: Oxford University Press, 4th edition,\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e提出課題・試験・成績評価の方法など\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAttendance and active participations(20%) Assignment (25%) Presentation (25%) Final paper (30 %)\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e履修上の注意\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eStudents are expected to have high proficiency in English to take this class. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch4 style=\"background-color: #ccecff; padding-left: 8px; font-weight: bold;\"\u003e授業計画\u003c/h4\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第1回 Course overview\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第2回 First language (L1) acquisition and bilingualism\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe will study the basics of language development of children, as well as the acquisition of two languages concurrently (bilingualism). We will cover different approaches to understanding L1 acquisition.\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第3回 Critical Period Hypothesis in L1 learning\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe will examine Critical (Sensitive) Period Hypothesis (CPH) which argues that there is an adequate time frame for L1 learning, after which acquisition becomes difficult. We will discuss the hypothesis visiting the actual cases and extend the concept to L2 learning.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第4回 L2 learning\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhat does L2 learning involve? We examine learning contexts (eg., classroom learning vs naturalistic learning) and learner language (e.g., Are students’ errors good or bad? If good, why can the errors be good? Can we guess what kinds of errors learners would make based on learners’ L1?). \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第5回 Cont. L2 learning\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eDo we all go through the same path of L2 language development? What are the developmental stages of L2 learning? Does learners’ L1 influence on the rate or route of the L2 learning? We also examine issues in the learning of L2 vocabulary, pragmatics and pronunciation. \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第6回 Individual differences in L2 learning\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe survey individual differences that might factor in L2 learning such as intelligence, aptitude, gender, and personality. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eDoes motivation influence in L2 learning? What types of motivation or learning ‘belief’ would facilitate L2 learning? We also discuss age factors revisiting CPH we studied in the 3rd week. \u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第7回 L2 learning theories\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe study various L2 learning theories: \u003cbr\u003e The behaviourist perspective \u003cbr\u003e The innatist perspective \u003cbr\u003e The cognitive perspective \u003cbr\u003e The sociocultural perspective\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第8回 Observing learning and teaching in L2 classroom\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe compare differences in naturalistic setting and institutional setting in L2 learning. Also we enquire how to observe L2 classroom by going over some L2 classroom observation schemes such as COLT (Communicative Orientation for Language Teaching). We investigate differences between structure based teaching and communicative L2 instructions.\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第9回 L2 learning in classroom (L2 teaching methodology)\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eStudents learn various L2 teaching methodologies and theories that motivated such methodologies. We discuss feasibility and pros and cons of each teaching method in groups.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第10回 Final Presentations\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第11回 Final Presentations\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第12回 Final Presentations\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第13回 ゲストスピーカー（補講）\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第14回 課題\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"color: #856a5d;\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n  \u003cp\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003chr\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003cu\u003e第15回 課題\u003c/u\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003cp style=\"colo